Gov. Inuwa Yahaya of Gombe State says Nigeria lost a dedicated  administrator by the demise of Mallam Abba Kyari, Chief of Staff to  President Muhammadu Buhari. Yahaya expressed the sadness in a statement signed by his Senior
Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Mr Ismaila Misilli, in Gombe
on Saturday. “Nigeria has indeed lost a fine and dedicated gentleman, a patriot
and a reliable administrator, who was always mindful of his duties and
responsibilities,” he said. The governor  said that  the late chief of staff would be remembered
for his exemplary leadership, effective service, dedication and loyalty. “On behalf of the Government and people of Gombe State, I wish to
extend our deepest condolences to Mr President, the family of the
deceased and the government and people of his home state, Borno, over
this great loss,”  he said. Yahaya prayed that the Almighty God would grant Kyari rest and give
his family and the nation at large the fortitude to bear his death.
